Welcome! 🤓

Hello and welcome to my personal webpage.
I'm Paulina Moskwa, Computer Vision and Artificial Intelligence researcher.

After graduating with a bachelor's degree in Mathematical Engineering at Politecnico di Milano in 2019, I further specialized my studies toward Artificial Intelligence by undertaking a master's degree in Mathematical Engineering with specialization in Statistical Learning, also at Politecnico di Milano. I am now in the process of writing my thesis. Besides, I am currently working as a Data Scientist at Cefriel in Milan, Italy.

My main fields of activity are Atificial Intelligence applications for Computer Vision tasks across different domains, focusing mainly on healthcare, automotive and industry fields.

Featured Projects

Real-Time Sign Language Detection ┃ More ↗️

Customized YOLOv5 for real-time sign language detection via PyTorch and OpenCV. Also, labeling and data drift issues have been addressed.

🏷️ Python, YOLOv5, PyTorch, OpenCV, LabelImg, Real-Time

Real-Time Social Distancing Detector ┃ More ↗️

Transfer learning YOLOv5 for real-time social distancing detection and people counting via PyTorch and OpenCV. Furthermore, the geometry of the environment is discussed.

🏷️ Python, YOLOv5, PyTorch, OpenCV, Real-Time Detection

Pediatric Pneumonia Chest X-Ray ┃ More ↗️

Deep learning - P​yTorch - CNN model to classify (and therefore predict) pediatric chest X-ray with pneumonia versus without pneumonia.

🏷️ Python, PyTorch, CNN Image Classification, Medical

Wildfire Smoke Detection ┃ More ↗️

Deep learning - PyTorch - model to detect the first signs of smoke from a forest fire, with the ultimate hope of dispatching a drone to douse it with water before it gets out of control.

🏷️ Python, PyTorch, Faster R-CNN, Object Detection

Face Mask CNN ┃ More ↗️

Deep learning - TensorFlow - CNN model to classify (and thus predict) if all people, some people or none are wearing face masks.

🏷️ Python, Tensorflow, Keras, CNN, Explainable AI

Generalized Linear Models ┃ More ↗️

Collection of end-to-end regression problems: simulation and real-case analyses of linear regression, logistic regression and poisson regression.

🏷️ Python, Scikit-Learn, Statsmodels, GLMs, Regression

R-Stats ┃ More ↗️

Easy-to-use collection of statistical methods and techniques implemented in R on toy-dataset. A deepening of this work, involving some real-case scenarios, is planned for the future.

🏷️ R, Applied Statistics, Nonparametric Statistics

Classifiers Comparison ┃ More ↗️

WebApp with the goal of comparing different binary classifiers from the python Scikit-learn library. No in-depth knowledge of classifiers or programming is required.

🏷️ Python, Scikit-Learn, Streamlit, Interactive WebApp

Volcanic Eruptions Visualization ┃ More ↗️

WebApp with the goal of testing several interactive map features. It is possible to navigate the map and observe where volcanic eruptions occurred from 2015 to 2022.

🏷️ Python, Geospatial, Streamlit, Interactive WebApp

Breast Cancer Classification ┃ More ↗️

Three analyses on the Breast Cancer Wisconsin dataset: EDA, dimensionality reduction (PCA, tSNE), classification (logistic regression, kNN, random forest, XGBoost).

🏷️ Python, Scikit-Learn, Classification, Medical

Deep Learning Code Generator ┃ More ↗️

WebApp with the aim of facilitating the writing of the code needed to create a convolutional neural network in TensorFlow for image classification.

🏷️ Python, TensorFlow, Keras, Streamlit, Code WebApp

Kidnapping Hobi ┃ More ↗️

Python implementation of the infinite runner game via PyGame. This will be the starting point for future reinforcement learning projects.

🏷️ Python, PyGame, Infinite Runner, Game
